The Alema of Warri Kingdom, Chief Oritsejolomi Uduaghan, has donated food items and other palliatives to 500 communities in the 25 local government areas of Delta State, to cushion the effect of the lockdown triggered by the novel coronavirus pandemic. Delta is one of the states currently on extended lockdown after recording three cases with one death, while 20 other contacts are being traced. The distribution of food items to vulnerable communities commenced on Monday. The items include cattle, thousands of bags of rice, garri, tubers of yam, and gallons of oil.